Package analysis

Class compareHoneypots

java.lang.Object
analysis.compareHoneypots
public class compareHoneypots
extends java.lang.Object
Compares two sets of honeypot solutions on a larger independent sample.
Author:
Sudesh Agrawal (sudesh@utexas.edu). Last Updated: February 16, 2021.

    • evaluateHoneypotsOnFalseNegativeModel

      public void evaluateHoneypotsOnFalseNegativeModel​(graph g, java.util.List<org.javatuples.Pair<parameters,​parameters>> compareParams, int outSampleSize) throws java.lang.Exception
      Evaluates two sets of honeypots for the pairs of parameters provided on a larger independent sample. Assumption: False negative probability in the second parameter of the pair is the correct one.
      Parameters:
      g - network graph
      compareParams - list of pairs of parameters for which the set of honeypots are to be compared
      outSampleSize - number of virus spread sample paths for evaluating the two sets of honeypots.
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - thrown if the label of a node in g is a negative integer.

    • getSemiHammingDistance

      private int getSemiHammingDistance​(graph g, java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> honeypots1, java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> honeypots2)
      This method returns half of the hamming distance between the two sets of honeypots.
      Parameters:
      g - network graph
      honeypots1 - the first set of honeypots
      honeypots2 - the second set of honeypots.
      Returns:
      half of the hamming distance between the two sets.

    • writeToCSV

      public void writeToCSV​(java.lang.String filename, boolean append) throws java.io.IOException
      Writes results of evaluateHoneypotsOnFalseNegativeModel(graph, List, int) stored in mapParamsPairToObjectiveValues and mapParamsPairToSemiHammingDistance to csv file.
      Parameters:
      filename - path to output file
      append - true, if you wish to append to existing file; false, otherwise.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - thrown if error in input-output operation.
